codex
The new attribute filter path can return false positives from the text branch and false negatives for rows that predate projection declaration. These are correctness issues in the feature being introduced.

Full review comments:

- [P2] Apply attribute filters to the text branch too — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15b/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2472-2472
  When `SearchFilter.attributes` is set, only the vector phase-1 SQL gets the new `attr_<hex>=?` predicate; the FTS/text branches still call `text_hit_passes_filter` / `edge_fts_hit_passes_filter`, which only check the four existing metadata fields. In a hybrid search where a nonmatching document is returned by FTS, it can still appear in the final RRF results despite failing the attribute equality filter.

- [P2] Populate new attr columns for existing matching rows — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15b/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:13893-13896
  When a filterable projection is added to an existing corpus, `configure_projections` backfills `canonical_attributes`, then this reshape fills every newly desired vec0 attr column with `''`. Existing rows whose bodies already contain the attribute therefore fail every pre-KNN attribute filter until they are rewritten/re-embedded, causing false negatives immediately after declaring a filterable projection.
